Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity of barium uranate BaUO4 has been measured in the temperature range (1.9 to 1570) K in order to resolve the discrepancy between two existing low-temperature calorimetric studies on this compound. Our results are in good agreement with one of the two earlier studies, and the impact of this finding is discussed.
